{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Start negotiations now to Rejoin the EU",
        "additional_details": " We think it is time for the Government to Apply to Rejoin the European Union.\r\n\r\nWhile we might not get the same deal as before we nonetheless believe that it would reduce the damage caused by Brexit and help restore our influence by becoming a full member of the EU again. The UK is a large country but is still small in world terms. We feel that improving cooperation with our neighbours will help increase economic stability and strengthen international influence, since relying on distant partners alone is not sufficient. We firmly believe that our future is best secured as part of a strong, united and democratic Europe.",
        "background": "10 years after the Brexit referendum and 6 years after leaving the EU, it is clear to us that Brexit isn't working. We believe any benefits have been dwarfed by loss of influence, extra costs and the inefficiencies it has created. ",
